<br>
 True, it had been over a year since Dawn had stepped foot into the famed amazon city of Themiscrya. It was better that way. Her legend hadn't died, nor had the village she had brought to life died. Orio-Pata ran strong, and would one day be as strong as Themiscrya or Scynthia. The assassin just wasn't needed.<br>
<br>
 For a moment the assassin stretched, bringing her arms back behind her back, and then above her head. It was almost time. And in honor Dawn would fight alongside her amazon sisters again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=queenhera>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 223<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/03 2:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=45>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/lilhera.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New arrivals.</span><hr size=1> It was hard for Hera to resist the chanting in the wooden hut.  She had been upset that Hippolyte had left Themiscrya to fight at her father's side.  Ares had practically demanded it.  And Zeus was behind him.  As odd as that was, and Hera couldn't fight the both of them.  So, they got their way.<br>
<br>
As Hippolyte had followed her father, the amazon lost a bit of favour with the Queen of the Gods.  But, the nights the amazon had spent crying over her decision pulled at the heart strings of the immortal who had reared her.  <br>
<br>
Zeus had thought surely he had won one of Hera.  But, he was sorely mistaken.  But, even as the chanting was pulling her.  Hera didn't allow it to fully bring her to see Hippolyte.  Instead, she sent a simple message of approval.  A single peacock feather appeared in a shimmering light before the amazons. <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 776<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/03 3:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=46>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New arrivals.</span><hr size=1> The feather appearing before them was all Hippolyte needed.  She stopped her chanting and reached out, picking up the lonely feather.  Hipp would win back Hera...and the feather showed her promise.  Tucking the feather inside her leather bodice, she arose and turned around to see the amazons there.  &quot;Athelfi...Hera has given us her blessing, this day!&quot; <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
