<br>
Elektra tilted her head in respect and then turned around moving into the woods.  Her weapons were always prepared.  Sharpened each night to be ready for blood.  But, this attack could use a little something extra.  Elektra broke off branches and and began to fashion weapons from the wood.  Long spears would come in handy for the night. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marpeamzn>Marpe Amzn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#993300>(2/21/03 6:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/MarpeAmznrpg.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preparing for the attack</span><hr size=1> The guard had already taken off into the woods close to the Roman village.  Stepping quietly, she listened for any sound of danger.  Her eyes slowely covered the ground and the trees.  Much of the area seemed thick and perfect for an ambush.  But, there was not set trail. There were three in fact, all seeming to go in the direction of the Black Sea.  <br>
<br>
A snap caught Marpe's attention and the amazon quickly scrambled up into the dense trees.  Watching soon, she found the source of the snap.  Three men were walking around searching for something, or someone.  They were grumbling in a language that Marpe could not quite understand.  Surely, they were the Romans.  For about an hour, the guard watched as the men moved back and forth.  It looked like they were searching for marks in the ground.  Perhaps, still looking for Hippolyte.<br>
